VXLAN VTEP: HER-tunnel-without-unicast-tunnel report
====================================================
Command : show platform trident vxlan vtep detail
Looking : remote VTEP IPs that have a HER tunnel but NO unicast vxlan tunnel
Verify  : each suspect IP's leading-zero-stripped hex key searched in
          "platform trident diag d chg MPLS_ENTRY_SINGLE" (present / ABSENT)

{% set ns = namespace(suspect_hosts=0, total_suspect=0, no_data=0, clean=0) -%}
{% for h in ansible_play_hosts_all | sort %}
{%- set r = hostvars[h].vtep_report | default(none) %}
{%- if r is none %}
[NO DATA] {{ h }} — device errored or returned nothing (see job log)
{%- set ns.no_data = ns.no_data + 1 %}
{%- elif r.suspect_count | int > 0 %}
[SUSPECT] {{ h }} — {{ r.suspect_count }}/{{ r.total }} VTEP(s): {{ r.suspect_ips | join(', ') }}
{%- for hit in hostvars[h].vtep_mpls_hits | default([]) %}
            {{ hit.ip }}  hex={{ hit.hex }}  MPLS_ENTRY_SINGLE: {{ ('present - ' ~ hit.match_count ~ ' line(s)') if hit.found else 'ABSENT' }}
{%- endfor %}
{%- set ns.suspect_hosts = ns.suspect_hosts + 1 %}
{%- set ns.total_suspect = ns.total_suspect + (r.suspect_count | int) %}
{%- else %}
{%- set ns.clean = ns.clean + 1 %}
{%- endif %}
{%- endfor %}

----------------------------------------------------
Devices total            : {{ ansible_play_hosts_all | length }}
Devices clean            : {{ ns.clean }}
Devices with suspect VTEP: {{ ns.suspect_hosts }}
Devices with no data     : {{ ns.no_data }}
Suspect VTEP entries     : {{ ns.total_suspect }}
----------------------------------------------------

Note: a HER tunnel with no unicast tunnel is a SCREENING signal, not a proven
fault. It can be legitimate when no remote MACs are yet learned behind that
VTEP. Investigate the listed devices/IPs; do not assume they are broken.
See README.md for what this means and next steps.
